- Be kind to one another?⁣
⁣
One thing I’ve realized especially after this pandemic started is that you have no idea what’s going on in another persons life, or how their day has been..⁣
⁣
During quarantine I’ve been more isolated and alone than I ever have before. The only people I might have spoken to in a day, could be the cashier in the store, or a colleague at work. ?⁣
⁣
When you’re not in this situation yourself, you don’t think about it, but when the only thing you hear in a day is “hey can you do a, b, and c” or just get told everything you’re doing wrong or should have done differently, it has the potential to truly ruin someone’s day.? Imagine someone being completely alone and the only person they talk to today is you, and all you told them was everything they could’ve done better.. ?⁣
⁣
It might seem like something superficial, but you have ?? ???? what’s going on in their life, so take care of each other.??‍??⁣
⁣
I think these times especially is hard on single people, and the elderly. We’ve lost social interactions, cultural events, and a lot of the things that makes you - you - is put on hold.? It’s been a time full of stress and uncertainty, which again reflects on our health and well-being?⁣
⁣
This post goes to everyone out there who are lonely and are struggling during this pandemic. ? ???? ???, ???’?? ??? ?????. We’ve made it this far, and there’s brighter times ahead?? I’m always here if anyone needs to talk? ⁣

node.text:
I lived in Winterhaven growing up, a popular neighborhood in Tucson. We had grass in our front and back yard, rare for Tucson. 

Every Saturday we would get up and do chores. My favorite chore was anything outside. I especially loved mowing the lawn and raking the leaves. I have the best memories from those ten years living there and all the fun things we did as a family on the weekend! 

For the past year I’ve worked Saturdays. Though I don’t mind it, there is something I love about having that family time on a Saturday - playing, cleaning and lounging. I had fond memories of that growing up. 

Thankful that I will soon be working my last Saturday at the office! Thankful for my practice and being able to adjust my schedule and grateful for coaching that I have the opportunity to be flexible and change things up without having to stress about financial changes. 

We are making plans for our September Coach Mentorship and I’d love to have you there and help you live the life you desire! Send me a message and we can chat! 

.
.

3-BIG MYTHS ABOUT WIGHTLOSS ???‍??
---------------------------------------------------------------
{FOLLOW :- @rubuzzfitness }??‍??
{Credit :- @workoutsofficial }??
---------------------------------------------------------------
1. All calories are equal
----------------------------------------------------------------
The calorie is a measurement of energy. All calories have the same energy content.
However, this does not mean that all calorie sources have the same effects on your weight.
Different foods go through different metabolic pathways and can have vastly different effects on hunger and the hormones that regulate your body weight.
For example, a protein calorie is not the same as a fat or carb calorie.
Replacing carbs and fat with protein can boost your metabolism and reduce appetite and cravings Also, calories from
whole foods like Fruit tend to be much more filling than calories from refined foods, such as candy.

2. Supplements can help you lose weight
-----------------------------------------------------------------
The weight loss supplement industry is massive.
Various companies claim that their supplements have dramatic effects, but they’re rarely very effective when studied.
The main reason that supplements work for some people is the placebo effect. People fall for the marketing tactics and want the supplements to help them lose weight, so they become more conscious of what they eat.
That said, a few supplements have a modest effect on weight loss. The best ones may help you shed a small amount of weight over several months.
-
LIKE ??& TAG ?? YOUR 3 FRIENDS
-
3. Carbs make you fat
------------------------------------------------------------
Low carb diet can aid weight loss
In many cases, this happens even without conscious calorie restriction. As long as you keep carb intake low and protein intake high, you’ll lose weight
Even so, this does not mean that carbs cause weight gain. While the obesity epidemic started around 1980, humans have been eating carbs for a very long time.
In fact, whole foods that are high in carbs are very healthy.
On the other hand, refined carbs like refined grains and sugar are definitely linked to weight gain.

node.text:
Recyclable, bio-degradable, compostable is not the same thing as plastic-free. ?
?????????
Pandemic life has made it easier for us to embrace a plastic-free, non-disposable, low-waste lifestyle. Plastic straws? How about regular ol’ coffee mug. Reusable containers? Well, duh. We’re eating in every day. This lack of mobility has gotten us into the habit of leaning less on on-the-go, and more on do-it-yourself. And honestly, it’s pretty chill. ?
?????????
Things we’re sad to give up: Gum and juice. Turns out gum is made of a synthetic rubber. And juice is something that will always come in a wasteful/harmful container, plus we can easily make it at home with less sugar. ?
?????????
WHEN YOU’RE ABOUT TO CHECK OUT?, TAKE A STEP BACK AND THINK OF NEMO Y’ALL. ?
?????????
Check out @plasticfreejuly and @plasticfreemermaid for more ideas!??
?????????

node.text:
A favourite staple since always- chilli paneer burger!
So this is what i do with my left over chilli paneer~
I cut a burger bun into halves.. toss and fry the upper side in butter. Once done,add a layer of chilli paneer to the bottom bun(swipe to see picture),a cheese slice and then topped with a fried egg.then cover it with the upper side of bun. Add butter to a pan and place the burger in it. Cook in medium flame for a while(so that the cheese melts well) and you are ready!
.
.
For the chilli paneer-
Take a bowl,add 250 gms small cubed paneer,salt,soy sauce,kashmiri red chilli powder,salt and 3 tbsp cornflour with some water. Mix n coat well. Fry it . Heat oil in a pan,add chopped garlic and green chillies( I didn’t have both today,but the taste still came out to be great). Add lot of thinly sliced onion and once properly cooked,add salt,soy sauce,green chilli sauce and tomato sauce with 1/4 tsp sugar. Add paneer to it and mix well. You are good to go!
.
.
.

node.text:
Hey! Welcome to the first post on my new page. I've been playing guitar for a while and have shared lots of videos to my private account over time, but thought it was about time to share the passion publicly! 

I mainly play guitar but  enjoy tinkering on the bass, keyboard and a liittle bit of vocals ? Yes, there are LOTS of players on Insta already, why another one? Good question- no good reason other than I love it, love making videos and recordings and I love sharing them ? 

Here's the most recent video I made, a cover of Real Love Song by Nothing But Thieves with my mate @alexsibillin . NBT have done some cool 'In Solitude' sessions while in quarantine, so we thought we'd do the same.

Enjoy and thanks for stopping by! 

••••••••••

And now, it is due to this lockdown that I feel demotivated and superduper lazy all the time. I don’t even feel like getting up and doing anything.
It is rightly said, excess of anything is bad?
All this is affecting my health, physically and mentally.
But, I am trying my best to stay positive all this while. 
To anyone who is reading this and is feeling the same, you are not alone. 
#thistooshallpass ??
Stay safe?

This might not be a instagram-able pic or post. But still posting cause it is a memorable one for me...

I have been suffering from metastatic thyroid cancer for 6 years and as a side effect for the last 4years I have been facing tremendous anxiety, panic attack and depression.

In 2020 I shifted to a whole new country leaving my parents for the first time. Just one week after stepping on Ireland it got locked down. This quarantine was really hard for my mental health

Due to the lockdown and shifting I could not do my check up for a long time. Some of my reports came really bad. Also my I was facing some swelling. GP gave me some intensive test to check if everything is alright. 

Before the night of tests, I was having cold feet. I started breaking thinking what will happen it something bad comes. How will I start the process allover again that too without my family all alone! Why breathing is so difficult for some!

Same happened the next day when I was in doctor's office. I was there early and to stay in denial I wanted to go back without the test. Then To calm down I sat in the starbucks, thought a lot of thing and did the test.

You can see the despair in my face.... it was a complex feeling. Today the report came. It is good this time! I am relieved but thought of keeping this as a memory of my struggle inside ....

You said some excellent and acceptable things on happiness....so be happy.?....you look more beautiful when you are smiling??

Happiness-
We tend to forget how important happiness is and get consumed with our own negative feelings of doom and gloom from time to time too. Furthermore, we sometimes don’t consciously realise we are doing this to ourselves.

Why Happiness is Important

Although we may sometimes neglect to cultivate our own happiness, feeling happy is intrinsically important. If we are happy it has added knock on effects and benefits. These include us becoming more compassionate and feeling healthier both physically and emotionally. We become more creative, witty, energetic and fun to be around and it can also lead us to become more financially successful.
°
Very few of us live our lives in complete isolation. We will have partners, families, friends and work colleagues with whom we interact on a daily basis so if we’re happy, then it’s likely to mean that they’ll feel happier too. Therefore, through our own happiness, we are actually giving something to other people too and enabling them to feel happy as well.
°
So how is Happiness Attained?

For happiness to be attained, it’s important to be open and willing to the concept that it can be attained. For us to do this, we need to rid ourselves of the negative energies which occur in our lives on a regular basis and which cause us to feel unhappy or at best, make us feel as though we are simply existing or drifting through life..
°
Make it a Trend
Post it on your story mention the page and use #BeHappyBeHealthy

node.text:
My first quarantine 18-course tasting menu delivery from @mifunenewyork almost two months ago. Price: 130.65 USD plus tax. There might be variations on the menu now. 
?
The appetizers were very summery and light, especially the leeks vinaigrette, beef tatami with garlic ponzu sauce and even the creamy and mild turnip gratin. It’s totally out of my expectation that they had lots of umami and leeks could be that yummy. The memory of this refreshing flavour lingered for a while and made me order the appetizers at Mifune’s patio dining. Last time when I visited Mifune, they told me we could order any dish from the tasting if not on the patio menu.
?
For the mains, I think I damaged the meat by an improper temperature and reheating process. The beef was tender and meaty even served cool but (after I ? pan fried it) the duck breast lost its moisture and was too chewy. The squid ink Bouillabaisse rice I tried at its outdoor dining was far much better and had a strong aroma. Really hope Mifune can provide some simple preparation steps for someone like me who was not very good at cooking and like mains served warm. I like the roasted vegetables but (understandable) it was lack of the aroma of charcoal compared to the outdoor dining version which was so flavourful.
?
What I did with my leftover: 
I didn’t notice the portion was for 3-4 people and I finished all by myself... Of course, I divided the 18-course tasting menu into several meals.  It would be a super fun food preparation experience for a party. However, I prepared all these dishes only by myself, it was overwhelming. For the leftover, I made myself a healthy Japanese breakfast: congee, beef tataki, smoked salmon, turnip gratin and mushroom kimpura. Then, I turned the squid ink bouillabaisse into a washoku dish topped with sunny side up egg, inspired by Loco Moco at AOI kitchen. If you have no one to share the tasting with, haha enjoy your own unique leftover creation series. 
?
unforgettable and enjoyable experience during my quarantine days!

[ Chilling ] “Look at the trees, look at the birds, look at the clouds, look at the stars and if you have eyes you will be able to see that the whole existence is joyful. Everything is simply happy. Trees are happy for no reason; they are not going to become prime ministers or presidents and they are not going to become rich and they will never have any bank balance. Look at the flowers — for no reason. It is simply unbelievable how happy flowers are.” Osho.

Parte de acampar es poder tener ese momento con uno mismo para observar a nuestro alrededor y saber valorar el momento y cada momento en nuestra vida, asi? como las cosas buenas como las no tan buenas que pasamos, Y si lo disfrutamos con una copa de vino ? @demuertewine mejor au?n, para abrir el entendimiento!!!

Credits : @me_loves_cooking
• • • • • •
recipe- spicy chicken fry..
.
.
First of all marinade chicken pieces with a bit of chili powder salt roasted cumin powder, one crushed tomato (grind it in a blender/ grinder) and a pinch of sugar, set aside for 20-30mins..
.
In a nonstick pan, add ghee and chicken pieces and fry till golden.. push them to a side and add curry leaves, julienned lemongrass, cumin seeds, cinnamon sticks, cardamoms, sliced onions, sliced green chilies ginger garlic paste, capsicum and fry till fragrant.. when the onions turn translucent push the chicken back and mix everything well.. add chili flakes, chili powder, roasted cumin powder and few crushed tomatoes (grind without water).. adjust salt, let the tomatoes cook till the oil starts to separate, and chicken is cooked.. serve hot..
.
